  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fluid challenge is often carried out in critical ill patients. Its responsiveness usually
      requires invasive monitoring. To use non-invasive methods is very tempting. Investigators
      hypothesize that transcutaneous pO2,transcutaneous pCO2 and Central Venous SO2 variations
      provide feasible estimation on fluid responsiveness in critical ill patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
