    <description>Adult patients (at least 18 years of age) with refractory hypotension secondary to sepsis who, at the discretion of treating physicians, required fluid challenge in the presence of invasive hemodynamic monitoring. Refractory hypotension was defined as need of vasopressors to maintain systolic blood pressure (SBP) no less than 90 mmHg despite adequate fluid resuscitation.</description>
